[From the above weekly report, unfortunately the transmission of WPV1 in Pakistan and Afghanistan continue as seen by the confirmation of new cases of polio associated with WPV1 infection in the past week. Likewise, unfortunately the transmission of cVDPVs (types 1, 2, and perhaps 3) continues with newly confirmed cases reported in Papua New Guinea and Somalia during the past week. The good news is the absence of newly confirmed cases reported in the DRC and Nigeria, but given the insecurities in the affected zones of both these countries, delayed reporting would not be unexpected.

I highly recommend readers continue on to part [2] of this post for an excellent commentary from Prof. Dr. T Jacob John related to the cVDPV1 outbreak ongoing in Papua New Guinea.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

